To build these software versions (or better) are required:

 -- CMake 2.4.3
 -- Qt 4.2.0
 -- OpenBabel 2.1

If you do an install of Avogadro it should automatically have the 
correct paths for loading all the plugins:

$CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX/lib/avogadro/{tools|extensions|engines}

You don't have to install avogadro, though. If you are running 
Avogadro from the build directory you should still setup your environment 
accordingly.  The important environment variables
and suggested values are:

AVOGADRO_TOOLS=$BUILD_DIR/libavogadro/src/tools
AVOGADRO_ENGINES=$BUILD_DIR/libavogadro/src/engines
AVOGADRO_EXTENSIONS=$BUILD_DIR/avogadro/src/extensions

To make you life a bit easier add these lines to your ~/.bashrc

export AVOBUILD_DIR=$HOME/build/avo
export AVOGADRO_TOOLS=$AVOBUILD_DIR/libavogadro/src/tools
export AVOGADRO_ENGINES=$AVOBUILD_DIR/libavogadro/src/engines
export AVOGADRO_EXTENSIONS=$AVOBUILD_DIR/avogadro/src/extensions
alias avo="$AVOBUILD_DIR/avogadro/src/avogadro"
